    {% endif %}

    {%- comment -%} Top bar {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="os-hero-topbar">
      <div class="os-hero-tag">Project / Polaris Car Care // Chicago, IL</div>
      <div class="os-hero-topbar-right">Est. 2025 — Doc. 001</div>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%} Title + info {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="os-hero-title-wrap">
      <h1 class="os-hero-title">
        Built <span class="os-hero-title-dim">From</span><br>Scratch.
      </h1>

      <div class="os-hero-info">
        <p class="os-hero-desc">{{ section.settings.hero_subhead | default: 'Two guys from Chicago who got tired of paying $40 for a towel — and decided to build something better. This is how Polaris Car Care started.' }}</p>

        <p class="os-hero-quote">
          "Our goal isn't to be the <em>cheapest</em> brand.
          It's to be the <em>most honest</em> one."
        </p>

        <p class="os-hero-annotation">
          — Antanas Kubilius &amp; Jacob Klepacki<br>
          Co-Founders, Polaris Car Care<br>
          Chicago, Illinois / 2025
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%} Bottom meta bar {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="os-hero-meta">
      <div class="os-hero-meta-item">
        <strong>Est.</strong>
        2025
      </div>
      <div class="os-hero-meta-item">
        <strong>Location</strong>
        Chicago, Illinois
      </div>
      <div class="os-hero-meta-item">
        <strong>Founders</strong>
        Antanas K. &amp; Jacob K.
      </div>
      <div class="os-hero-meta-item">
        <strong>Flagship</strong>
        The Nova — 1200 GSM
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%} ── THE PROBLEM ── {%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="os-problem bp-bg os-fade">
    <div class="os-section-annotation">01 — The Problem</div>

    <div class="os-problem-intro">
      <h2 class="os-big-question">
        Why <em>Does</em><br>
        Premium<br>
        Mean<br>
        Over&shy;priced?
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p class="os-problem-body">
          We were buying products from well-known brands and couldn't stop asking the same question: why does a microfiber towel cost nearly $40 before shipping? And why are so many "affordable" options clearly cutting corners on the things that actually matter — fiber quality, absorbency, paint safety?
        </p>
        <br>
        <p class="os-problem-body">
          Founded by <strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85)">Antanas Kubilius and Jacob Klepacki</strong>, Polaris Car Care was built on a simple realization — quality automotive detailing tools shouldn't be a luxury reserved for professionals or high-budget consumers. As active members of the car community themselves, the founders saw firsthand how many enthusiasts were forced to choose between overpriced "top-tier" brands or cheaper products that simply didn't perform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="os-problem-grid">
      <div class="sticky sticky--y sticky-r2">
        <span class="sticky-title">The real problem ↓</span>
        <p>"Why does a microfiber towel cost nearly $40 before shipping?"</p>
        <div class="sticky-quote">That question became the foundation of Polaris.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="sticky sticky--p sticky-r3">
        <span class="sticky-title">Budget options 🚫</span>
        <p>The cheap stuff falls apart after 3 washes. Fibers scratch your paint. No consistency. Can't trust it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sticky sticky--b sticky-r1n">
        <span class="sticky-title">The gap we saw 💡</span>
        <p>Nobody was building for <em>us</em> — young enthusiasts who love cars but can't afford $40 per towel. So we did.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%} ── HOW WE BUILT IT ── {%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="os-diagram bp-bg os-fade">
    <div class="os-section-annotation">02 — How We Built It</div>

    <h2 class="os-diagram-heading">
      Built by Enthusiasts.<br>
      <span style="color:rgba(100,160,255,0.4);">Tested in the</span><br>
      Real World.
    </h2>

    <div class="os-steps">
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">01</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">The Idea</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">Two co-founders fed up with the market. One handles brand strategy and business — the other brings professional detailing expertise. Different skills, same obsession.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">02</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Real Testing</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">Every product is first tested on the founders' own vehicles. Jacob has worked alongside detailers servicing exotic and luxury cars — if it doesn't pass his standard, it doesn't get sold.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">03</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Community Review</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">Before any product hits the store, it goes through friends and trusted voices in the local car community. Real feedback. No marketing fluff.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="os-step">
        <div class="os-step-num">04</div>
        <div class="os-step-title">Honest Pricing</div>
        <p class="os-step-body">We reverse-engineer from the customer backward. What performance do you need? What's a fair price? We refuse to inflate margins at the expense of access to the hobby.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="os-stamp-wrap">
      <div class="os-stamp-quote">
        "Our goal isn't to be the cheapest brand.<br>
        <span style="color:rgba(100,160,255,0.5);">It's to be the most honest one."</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-stamp">
        <span class="os-stamp-text">REAL WORLD</span>
        <span class="os-stamp-text--big">TESTED</span>
        <span class="os-stamp-text">✓ APPROVED</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%} ── THE STANDARD ── {%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="os-standard bp-bg os-fade">
    <div class="os-section-annotation">03 — The Standard</div>

    <div class="os-standard-grid">
      <div class="os-standard-left">
        <h2 class="os-standard-heading">
          If It Doesn't Pass<br>
          <span style="color:rgba(100,160,255,0.35);">Jacob's Test.</span><br>
          It Doesn't Ship.
        </h2>
        <p class="os-standard-body">
          Jacob Klepacki brings real professional detailing experience to Polaris. He's worked alongside detailers who service high-end vehicles — including exotic and luxury cars — which means he knows exactly what a product needs to do under real conditions, not just in a lab.
        </p>
        <p class="os-standard-body" style="margin-top:20px;">
          Every Polaris product is first tested on the founders' own vehicles. Then it goes to trusted friends inside the car community. Only after it passes both rounds does it ever get listed for sale. No shortcuts. No marketing fluff. Just real feedback from real enthusiasts.
        </p>
        <p class="os-standard-body" style="margin-top:20px;">
          This blend of business strategy and technical detailing knowledge is what lets Polaris balance performance, durability, and price without sacrificing any of the three.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="os-standard-right">
        <div class="os-checklist-label">Quality Control Checklist</div>
        <div class="os-checklist">
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
            <span class="os-check-mark">✓</span>
            <div>
              <div class="os-check-name">Absorbency</div>
              <div class="os-check-desc">Must pull water without streaking or smearing across paint</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
            <span class="os-check-mark">✓</span>
            <div>
              <div class="os-check-name">Paint Safety</div>
              <div class="os-check-desc">Zero marring on coated, ceramic, and PPF surfaces</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
            <span class="os-check-mark">✓</span>
            <div>
              <div class="os-check-name">Durability</div>
              <div class="os-check-desc">Holds up wash after wash — no fiber degradation after 30+ cycles</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="os-check-item os-check--pass">
            <span class="os-check-mark">✓</span>
            <div>
              <div class="os-check-name">Consistency</div>
              <div class="os-check-desc">Every unit performs the same as the sample. No batch variance</div>
